Program: Discovery
Title: Maths and the small world syndrome
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jrxgs
Last Broadcast Date: 27 August 1999
The maths behind how people are linked to one another. How maths can help tie us together and how a scientific paper 'The Small World Syndrome' has ramifications for both health and technology. A scientist who has been studying crickets that synchronise their chirps explains how maths helped his research. Show less